### Obsidian plugin (v0)
- `apps/obsidian-plugin/` — TS, esbuild. `npm run deploy` copies `main.js`+`manifest.json`
  into `vault/.obsidian/plugins/blackbox/`; enable in Obsidian community plugins.
- Status bar polls `/health` + `/skills/pending` (30s). Commands: Summarize active note,
  Triage active note, Review pending approvals (SuggestModal → draft review → approve/reject).
- Settings: orchestrator URL, API key. `main.js` is gitignored (build artifact).

### Crash recovery
- Startup logs stale `20-Active-Loops/` notes; `scan_recovery` classifies orphan (running,
  no live thread) vs stale_approval. `GET /api/v1/skills/recovery`,
  `POST /skills/recovery/resolve` {mark_failed|dismiss}, `blackbox recovery [--dismiss-all]`,
  dashboard Recovery panel.
- **Root cause of the 32 stale notes it found:** `ObsidianClient`/`VaultWatcher` now
  `.resolve()` the vault path — a relative `BLACKBOX_VAULT_PATH=../../vault` produced
  loop paths with `..` that `resolve_active_loop`'s traversal guard silently rejected,
  so notes never left `running`. Fixed + regression test.

### Sandbox Tier 1
- `core/sandbox/tier1.py` `run_tier1()`: allowlist (`BLACKBOX_SANDBOX_TIER1_ALLOWED`,
  default `git`), cwd jailed to vault, scrubbed env, hard timeout, no shell. Accidents not
  adversaries; real isolation is Tier 2 (WSL2).
- Approve an exec interrupt: `POST /api/v1/skills/interrupts/{id}/approve` — runs the recorded
  `argv` in Tier 1, but only if the skill declares `sandbox_tier: 1`. `/deny` clears it.
  exec interrupts now carry full `arguments` (incl. `argv`) for replay.

### Drivers (s4) quick facts
- Config: `vault/.system/drivers.json` — entries `{name, transport: stdio|sse, command, args, env_allow, tags, enabled}`; shipped examples are `enabled: false`
- Env is **allowlist-only** — `GEMINI_API_KEY` never crosses into a driver unless `env_allow` names it
- Skills opt in per tool: `tools: ["fs.read_file", "search.*"]` in skill YAML (closed by default)
- `tags: ["exec"]` on a driver → every tool denied with `ToolExecApprovalRequired` + IVT row (Tier 0 sandbox)
- API: `GET /api/v1/drivers/`, `POST /api/v1/drivers/remount`; `/health` has a `drivers` key
- Each driver runs in an owner task (anyio contexts must enter/exit in the same task); mounts happen in background at boot
- Pipeline steps consume tools via `node_tools:` (declarative calls, args templated
  from `{user_input}` + prior step outputs; results injected as step outputs)
- Proof skill: `summarize_note` (`graph: pipeline`, zero Python) reads any vault
  note through `vault_fs.read_note` and archives a summary — verified live
- `vault_fs` driver = our own read-only FastMCP server
  (`apps/orchestrator/tools/vault_fs_server.py`), jailed to the vault, no Node needed

**Ground rules:** kernel + user space in **one process**; keep `registry.py`; MCP replaces tools not graphs; no Docker/E2B default.

