### Adding a skill without Python (pipeline v1)
```yaml
# vault/.system/skill-definitions/my_skill.yaml
name: my_skill
graph: pipeline
system_prompt: |
  You are ...
nodes:
  - plan
  - draft
  - critic          # optional
  - human_approval  # optional — enables interrupt gate
  - finalize
node_prompts:        # optional — defaults generated from step id
  plan: "Plan the work for: {user_input}"
max_cost_per_run: 0.20
```

## Gemini
- Default model: `gemini-2.5-flash-lite`; paid tier in operator `.env` (100k/day, 0.2s pace)
- Budget ledger: per-model keys, counts every API attempt (not just 200)
- Degraded: clears after retry window; manual Armory runs proceed
- RAG: tolerant vault text encodings (Windows UTF-16)
- Free tier (if used): ~5 RPM, **20 RPD** — autonomous runs defer via IVT when reserve hit
- Do not health-probe Gemini every poll; embedding cache avoids re-embed on restart

## API quick reference
- `GET /api/v1/skills/interrupts` — pending IVT rows (budget, degraded, HITL, tool_exec)
- `GET /api/v1/skills/pending` — HITL approvals (`draft`, `confidence`)
- `GET /api/v1/skills/recovery` — stale active-loop notes
- `POST /api/v1/skills/recovery/resolve` — `{ path, action: mark_failed|dismiss }`
- `POST /api/v1/skills/interrupts/{id}/approve|deny` — Tier 1 exec (skill needs `sandbox_tier: 1`)
- `GET /api/v1/health` — budget snapshot + degraded flag

